The paper deals with visual saliency detection using deep learning architectures, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of handcrafted features and hierarchical integration, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of dilated convolutions, which is a technique commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE).
